text: is the name of the a Japanese space probe which was sent on an interplanetary mission.Sakigake was identical in construction and shape to Suisei, but carried a different payload. The launch was a project of the Institute of Space and Astronautical Science of the University of Tokyo. The satellite was launched on January 7, 1985.JAXA, "Catalogue of ISAS Missions" ; retrieved 2012-4-16. == References == == Other websites == * Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA), Sakigake (MS-T5) mission profile * NASA, Sakigake Category:Japanese satellites Category:1980s in spaceflight
